romise easy highways you promise","start":130.1,"end":134.84},{"text":"I won't lose you Now my faith ain't just a label it's","start":134.84,"end":139.22},{"text":"a lifeline when I choke And I don't just know about you","start":139.22,"end":144.74},{"text":"now I know Not a badge","start":144.74,"end":149.04},{"text":"not a checkbox not a baby in my head It's the real","start":149.36,"end":153.3},{"text":"God in the real dark holding me when I'm not strong yet","start":153.3,"end":159.1},{"text":"I thought I was a Christian but now I know It's more","start":159.1,"end":164.66},{"text":"than going through it it's letting you hold my soul You used","start":164.66,"end":170.54},{"text":"the hard times to show me you're close I thought I was","start":170.54,"end":175.44},{"text":"a Christian but now I know","start":175.44,"end":180.1},{"text":"Not just rescued in a moment","start":188.04,"end":191.06},{"text":"but remade with hope I thought I was a Christian but now","start":191.46,"end":198.74},{"text":"I know If you're listening I'm listening If you're near I'm not","start":198.74,"end":206.2},{"text":"alone I thought I was a Christian","start":206.2,"end":209.58},{"text":"but now I know","start":210.78,"end":213.66}],"duration":213.66,"plain_text":"I grew up in the echo of be good and believe Ceiling lights, old songs, and the air you couldn't leave I learned the names, learned the miracles, learned the rules, learned the tone But I kept you at a distance like a number in my phone Ark in the water, sea split wide, giants fall, and fear denied I memorized what you could do, but I never let you carry me through Then real life hit my front door and my mind fell apart Turns out knowing all the stories isn't the same as knowing your heart I thought I was a Christian, but now I know It's more than going through it, it's letting you hold my soul When everything was shaking, you were steady in the smoke I thought I was a Christian, but now I know I was angry, I was bargaining, counting loss like it's proof Saying, God, where are you hiding while you were walking in my shoes? You were in the call I finally made and the tears I couldn't stage And the friend who didn't preach to me just stayed and let me break I knocked hard on heaven's doorway with a fistful of fear And the door swung wide in mercy like you've been waiting here I thought I was a Christian, but now I know It's more than going through it, it's letting you hold my soul When everything was shaking, you were steady in the smoke I thought I was a Christian, but now I know So let the hard days keep talking, let the scars tell the truth You don't promise easy highways, you promise I won't lose you Now my faith ain't just a label, it's a lifeline when I choke And I don't just know about you, now I know Not a badge, not a checkbox, not a baby in my head It's the real God in the real dark holding me when I'm not strong yet I thought I was a Christian, but now I know It's more than going through it, it's letting you hold my soul You used the hard times to show me you're close I thought I was a Christian, but now I know Not just rescued in a moment, but remade with hope I thought I was a Christian, but now I know If you're listening, I'm listening If you're near, I'm not alone I thought I was a Christian, but now I know"}